President Donald J. Trump has appointed U.S. Coast Guard Rear Admiral Peter J. Brown as the Special Representative for Puerto Rico's Disaster Recovery. Admiral Brown will be responsible for coordinating the efforts of the United States Government to rebuild Puerto Rico's infrastructure and improve its resilience. The island was severely impacted by Hurricane Maria in 2017 and a series of earthquakes in January 2020. Admiral Brown will work with federal agencies, the White House, Puerto Rico officials, and Congress to ensure effective allocation of resources and address the concerns of the people. Prior to this role, Admiral Brown served as the Commander of the Seventh Coast Guard District and has over 34 years of experience in the Coast Guard.